WHEREAS, Iberville Parish Day at the state capitol provides an important
opportunity to strengthen relationships between parish and state leadership, promote the
parish's achievements, and advocate for its future.
THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED that the House of Representatives of the
Legislature of Louisiana does hereby designate Wednesday, April 15, 2026, as Iberville
Parish Day at the state capitol and does hereby express support for the continued
collaboration and strategic investment in infrastructure and economic development
initiatives that promote the sustained growth and prosperity of Iberville Parish and the
surrounding region.
